This code snippet showcases a simple book document class in LaTeX. The `\tableofcontents` command generates the ToC based on the `\chapter` and `\section` commands defined before it. Each chapter and section will contribute to the ToC as you build and compile your document. If you want each entry in the ToC to have hyperlinks that jump to the relevant page, ensure you are using the `hyperref` package with `\usepackage{hyperref}`.

